Undergraduate Application Status | UIC Admissions                  Explore UIC  Visit Virtually  Apply    S      Search Input     Submit        M       Undergraduate Application Status        Home  Undergraduate  Application Process  You are here     Home  Undergraduate  Application Process  You are here              Did you know?     DEPTH         i                     Due to the COVID-19 pandemic UIC continues to accept undergraduate first-year and transfer applications for the Fall 2020 semester.            Check Application Status    Now that you've applied, you can monitor your admission status online.  Check your status online . Within a day or two of applying, Common Application users receive a PIN number in the "UIC Application Acknowledgment" email that will activate their UIC application status portal.    Summer Session Applicants  Summer Session Only Applicants  Please visit the Summer Session website for instructions on checking the status of your application.  Intercampus Registrants  You will receive your decision letter by mail. If you have any questions regarding your application status, contact the Summer Session Office via email at Summer@uic.edu .                            Related Resources    Visit Campus  Explore UIC  Contact Admissions                    UnderGraduate      Graduate & Professional                 Office of Admissions  Main Office  1200 West Harrison Street Chicago, IL 60607-7161 Phone: (312) 996-4350 Contact UIC Admissions    Visitors Center  1220 West Harrison Street Chicago, IL 60607-7161 Phone: (312) 413-1726                 Mailing Address  Undergraduate  Office of Undergraduate Admissions (MC 018) University of Illinois at Chicago 1200 West Harrison Street, Suite 1100 Chicago, IL 60607-7161 Contact Undergraduate Admissions     Graduate & Professional  The graduate and professional application process is paperless. Please do not mail materials unless expressly requested. Contact Graduate and Professional Admissions         